a Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Whelton was born in 1320, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas de Whelton, was 31 and his mother, Isabella, was 18. He had at least 1 son. He died on 31 August 1361, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1320–31 August 1361":"1320–31. august 1361","1320–1361":"1320–1361","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1343–1383":"1343–1383","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1302–Female":"1302–Surnud","1302":"1302","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","31 August 1361":"31. august 1361","1290":"1290","Broadbridge, Sussex England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1320–31 August 1361":"1320–31. elokuuta 1361","1320–1361":"1320–1361","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1343–1383":"1343–1383","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1302–Female":"1302–Kuollut","1302":"1302","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","31 August 1361":"31. elokuuta 1361","1290":"1290","Broadbridge, Sussex England":"Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1320–31 August 1361":"1320–31 août 1361","1320–1361":"1320–1361","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1343–1383":"1343–1383","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1302–Female":"1302–Décédée","1302":"1302","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","31 August 1361":"31 août 1361","1290":"1290","Broadbridge, Sussex England":"Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas de Whelton est né en 1320, à Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Thomas de Whelton, avait 31 ans et sa mère, Isabella, avait 18 ans. Il a eu au moin